# Poolside CLI Environment Variables Reference
# 
# IMPORTANT: This file is for REFERENCE ONLY. 
# You do NOT need to copy or use this file directly.
#
# Poolside stores credentials in ~/.poolside/config.json
# Use the interactive setup: poolside setup
# Or set credentials directly: poolside config set <key> <value>
#
# Environment variables (POOLSIDE_*) take precedence over config file settings.
# This is useful for CI/CD pipelines.
#
# ================================
# Configuration Management
# ================================
#
# Resolution order (highest to lowest priority):
#   1. Environment variables (POOLSIDE_*)
#   2. ~/.poolside/config.json
#   3. Default values
#
# Commands:
#   poolside setup              - Interactive credential setup
#   poolside config             - View all credentials and presets
#   poolside config show        - Same as 'config' (alias)
#   poolside config set <k> <v> - Set a credential
#   poolside config get <key>   - Get a credential value
#   poolside config test        - Test all connections
#
# ================================
# AI Provider Configuration
# ================================
# POOLSIDE_AI_PROVIDER=openai
#   Choose your AI provider: "openai" (default) or "anthropic"
#
# POOLSIDE_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_api_key_here
#   Required if POOLSIDE_AI_PROVIDER=openai (or not set)
#   Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#   Config key: openaiApiKey
#
# POOLSIDE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your_anthropic_api_key_here
#   Required if POOLSIDE_AI_PROVIDER=anthropic
#   Get from: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#   Config key: anthropicApiKey
#
# POOLSIDE_AI_MODEL=gpt-5.2
#   Override the default model for your provider
#   OpenAI default: gpt-5.2
#   Anthropic default: claude-sonnet-4-20250514
#   Config key: aiModel
#
# POOLSIDE_AI_MAX_TOKENS=4000
#   Maximum tokens for AI responses
#   Config key: aiMaxTokens
#
# ================================
# Model Presets
# ================================
# POOLSIDE_PRESET=balanced
#   Set active preset via environment variable
#   Available built-in presets:
#     fast     - gpt-5.2 (OpenAI) - Quick tasks, lower cost
#     quality  - claude-sonnet-4-20250514 (Anthropic) - Best output quality
#     balanced - gpt-5.2 (OpenAI) - Good balance of speed/quality (default)
#     cheap    - gpt-3.5-turbo (OpenAI) - Lowest cost
#
# Manage presets with:
#   poolside config preset list          - Show all presets
#   poolside config preset use <preset>  - Switch active preset
#   poolside config preset add <name>    - Add custom preset
#   poolside config preset remove <name> - Remove custom preset
#
# ================================
# JIRA Configuration
# ================================
# POOLSIDE_JIRA_HOST=your-company.atlassian.net
#   Your JIRA hostname WITHOUT https://
#   Config key: jiraHost
#
# POOLSIDE_JIRA_USERNAME=your_jira_username
#   Your JIRA username/email
#   Config key: jiraUsername
#
# POOLSIDE_JIRA_PASSWORD=your_jira_password_or_pat
#   Your JIRA password or Personal Access Token (PAT recommended)
#   For PAT setup, run: poolside setup jira-pat
#   Config key: jiraPassword
#
# ================================
# GitHub Configuration
# ================================
# POOLSIDE_GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_token_here
#   GitHub Personal Access Token
#   Config key: githubToken
#
# Token Types:
#   Classic: https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   Fine-grained: https://github.com/settings/tokens?type=beta (recommended)
#
# Required Permissions (Fine-grained):
#   - Contents: Read
#   - Metadata: Read
#   - Pull requests: Read
#
# ================================
# Slack Integration (Optional)
# ================================
# POOLSIDE_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...
#   Slack webhook URL for posting summaries
#   Config key: slackWebhookUrl
#
# ================================
# Quick Setup Guide
# ================================
#
# Option 1: Interactive Setup (Recommended)
#   poolside setup
#
# Option 2: Direct Commands
#   poolside config set openaiApiKey sk-your-key-here
#   poolside config set jiraHost your-company.atlassian.net
#   poolside config set jiraUsername your_username
#   poolside config set jiraPassword your_password
#   poolside config set githubToken ghp_your_token
#
# Option 3: Environment Variables (for CI/CD)
#   export POOLSIDE_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
#   export POOLSIDE_JIRA_HOST=your-company.atlassian.net
#   # ... etc
